## Multi-Turn Codewalk Eval (Post Idle Signal Fix) — 2026-03-22

### Bugs found and fixed (3 bugs)

**Bug 1 — Lost idle signals (drain-before-send)**: The event loop goroutine used a
non-blocking send on the buffer-1 `idleCh` channel. During rapid Idle→Running→Idle cycles
from child notification processing, intermediate signals were silently dropped, causing the
final "all children done" idle to never reach the interactive loop.
Fix: drain-then-blocking-send pattern guarantees the latest signal is never lost.

**Bug 2 — Nested select deadlock**: The interactive loop had an inner select waiting for
stdin that couldn't see new `idleCh` signals from child-notification turns. After all
questions were sent, the loop blocked forever on stdin.
Fix: Flattened into a single `for/select` with a `promptReady` state flag. Both `idleCh`
and `stdinCh` are in the same select.

**Bug 3 — Child notification starvation (manager.go)**: Go's `select` randomly picked
between `followUpChan` and `childNotifyChan`, causing child completions to pile up during
rapid follow-ups.
Fix: Non-blocking drain of `childNotifyChan` before the blocking `select`.

### Also added
- `idle-children-active` vs `idle` status-fd protocol for eval script
- `SendFollowUp` retry with backoff in CLI (5 attempts, 500ms-2.5s)
- Extracted `runInteractiveLoop` with `interactiveLoopConfig` for testability
- 4 regression tests in `bramble/cmd/delegator/delegator_test.go`

Files changed: `bramble/cmd/delegator/delegator.go`, `bramble/cmd/delegator/delegator_test.go`,
`bramble/cmd/delegator/BUILD.bazel`, `bramble/session/manager.go`, `scripts/delegator-eval.py`

### Test results (codewalk eval via delegator-eval.py)

Questions: 11/11 | Elapsed: 166s (~2.8 min) | Cost: $0.69 total ($0.06/question)
Delegator: 13 turns, $0.69 | Child: 1 Gemini codetalk session, 2 turns
Tools used: start_session, get_session_progress, send_followup, Read

Flow: delegator queued 11 questions → spawned 1 codetalk child → read research file →
sent 1 follow-up for gaps → synthesized all 11 answers in Turn 13 → eval script received
"idle" (no children) → sent quit → clean exit.

### Quality assessment
All 11 answers use inverted pyramid style: lead sentence with the key takeaway, then
mechanism, then detail. No markdown headers in answers. Each answer is a prose paragraph
that reads naturally aloud. Topics covered: session lifecycle, mutex ordering, delegator
vs planner/builder, error paths, SendFollowUp internals, streaming pipeline, codetalkRunner,
providerRunner dedup, ReconcileTmuxSessions, concurrency gotchas, adding a new session type.

### Verdict
PASS — all 3 idle signal bugs fixed and verified with 4 regression tests. 11/11 questions
answered in 166s at $0.69. Clean exit via status-fd protocol. No regressions.

